title.narrative: Scaling up malaria prevention, control, and treatment through all sectors in Liberia

description.narrative: Liberia - Malaria - Plan International, Inc. - Plan International Liberia. This program has the following goals: By end of 2025, reduce malaria burden by 75% (11% overall prevalence) compared to 2016 (45% prevalence). The objectives of this program are: By end of 2025, reduce malaria mortality rates by at least 75% (43/100,000 population) compared to 2016 (172/100,000 population). By end of 2025, reduce malaria case incidence by at least 75% (95/1,000 population) compared to 2016 (380/1,000 population). By end of 2025, promote and maintain a culture of evidence-based decision making to achieve malaria program performance at all levels. By end of 2025, strengthen and maintain capacity for program management, coordination and partnership to achieve malaria program performance at all levels
